# Simplifying the Data Migration Framework

You've made a good move by consolidating the public API in the runner.go file. To further simplify this framework by eliminating unnecessary complexity, here are my recommendations:

## Components to Simplify or Eliminate

### 1. Merge registry.go into runner.go
The registry is a simple implementation that doesn't need its own file. Since your RunMigrations is now in runner.go, you can consolidate:

```go
// In runner.go
type registry struct {
    migrations []Migration
    lookup     map[string]Migration
}

var defaultRegistry = &registry{
    migrations: []Migration{},
    lookup:     make(map[string]Migration),
}

// Register adds a migration to the registry
func Register(migration Migration) {
    defaultRegistry.lookup[migration.ID()] = migration
    defaultRegistry.migrations = append(defaultRegistry.migrations, migration)
}

// RunMigrations would stay here as it already is
```

### 2. Simplify storage.go
The storage implementation is quite straightforward. Consider:

- Inline the storage implementation directly in runner.go
- Remove the separate storage struct and just use Consul client directly
- Move migrationInfo and migrationHistory to migration.go

### 3. Eliminate base_migration.go
The BaseMigration implementation is very simple and could be moved into migration.go:

```go
